text: The AfCFTA Business Forum is a large-scale event aimed at promoting business and investment opportunities in the African Continental Free Trade Area (AfCFTA).
It will be organized by the AfCFTA Secretariat, in collaboration with the Government of South Africa, and is scheduled to take place from April 16 to 19, 2023 in Cape Town, South Africa.

The main objectives of the AfCFTA Business Forum are: to create awareness of current business and investment opportunities in the AfCFTA among Africa’s business community, to connect businesses to funding opportunities for AfCFTA value chains, to establish a private sector engagement platform for continued consultations on private sector needs in the implementation of the AfCFTA, to promote a private sector-friendly environment especially for MSMEs led by women and youth, to unlock more accessible and affordable access to finance and markets.

Who can participate in the AfCFTA Business Forum: Africa’s private sector, Strategic investors, Financial institutions, Investment promotion agencies, Business councils, Chambers of commerce, Multinational corporations, African women and youth business organisations, African Heads of States, African Governments Officials especially those involved in trade regulation, promotion & facilitatior, Regional Economic Communities, Academia, National, Regional and International media

What is the format of the AfCFTA Business Forum: The AfCFTA Business Forum will include plenaries, roundtables, fireside chats breakout sessions, and side events highlighting policies and investment opportunities in focus sectors, as well as spaces for one-to-one business meetings, deal rooms, investment promotion, networking breaks, cultural and social events including an award ceremony, and a creative showcase. There will also be investor pitches and the opportunity to explore business opportunities in South Africa and Cape Town. The AfCFTA Business Forum will highlight the following sectors: agro-processing, automotive, pharmaceuticals, transportation and logistics, and digital trade, among others.

How can I participate in the AfCFTA Business Forum? To participate in the AfCFTA Business Forum, you can register on the event's official website. More information on the registration process and requirements is available on the website.  The registration website will go live early-mid March. Once registration is open, you can complete the process through the website.

The Government of South Africa’s commitment to supporting the implementation of the AfCFTA and the hosting of this Forum is a testament to their commitment to promoting economic integration and growth on the continent.

This presents an opportunity for businesses to explore the rich and diverse opportunities available in South Africa and the wider African region. The country is a gateway to the African continent, with a well-developed infrastructure, a highly skilled workforce, and a strong financial sector.

The AfCFTA Business Forum provides a platform for businesses to connect with local partners, explore investment opportunities, and learn about the policies and initiatives aimed at promoting trade and investment within the AfCFTA.

Participants at the AfCFTA Business Forum will not only have the opportunity to network and engage with key players in the African business community, but also to experience the vibrant culture and hospitality of Cape Town. The city offers a wealth of opportunities for cultural exchange, from its museums and art galleries, to its rich musical heritage, and delicious cuisine.
This is an opportunity to expand business horizons, make meaningful connections, and forge long-lasting relationships.
The Forum will include a range of activities such as plenaries, roundtables, fireside chats, and side events to highlight policies and investment opportunities in the focus sectors.
There will also be spaces for one-to-one business meetings, sponsored breakfasts and luncheons, deal rooms, investment promotion, and networking breaks.
A cultural and social program, including an award ceremony, a gala dinner, and a creatives showcase, will also be held to add to the experience.

The Forum seeks a broad participation of Africa’s private sector, strategic investors, financial institutions, investment promotion agencies, business councils, chambers of commerce, multinationals, African women and youth business organizations, as well as Heads of Government, Regional Economic Communities (RECs), academia, regional and international media, and AfCFTA Partners.
With the beautiful city of Cape Town as the host, there will also be a strong tourism component to the Forum.
The AfCFTA Business Forum is a landmark event as it is the first business forum to take place after the launch of the guided trade initiative.
This means that the instruments necessary for trading under the AfCFTA have already been put into place and are ready to be utilized.
Businesses and investors can take advantage of the opportunities created by the AfCFTA to expand their reach, connect with new partners and customers, and access new markets.
Moreover, 2023 is designated as the Year of the AfCFTA under the African Union theme of “Accelerating the AfCFTA.”
This makes the AfCFTA Business Forum a unique opportunity to take advantage of all the machinery of the African Union and Agenda 2063 to promote business and investment in Africa.

The African Union’s commitment to promoting economic integration on the continent is reflected in its choice of theme and the AfCFTA Business Forum provides a platform to showcase this commitment and to encourage investment and trade within the AfCFTA.
This is a crucial moment for businesses, investors, and governments to come together to discuss, collaborate and create a shared vision for the future of African trade.
Join us in Cape Town and take advantage of this opportunity to network, connect, and explore the limitless possibilities that the AfCFTA has to offer. Open registration begins 7th February, 2023.
